and that an SIS is therefore not required, the NYISO will notify TPAS\n1225-following a determination that an SIS is not required for a project.\n1226-2.4.2.4. Getting Started \u2013 System Impact Study Request\n1227-\n1228-The TO proposing the project (i.e., the Eligible Customer) initiates the SIS process by submitting a SIS\n--\n1532-3.1. Introduction\n1533-Excluding the NYISO\u2019s transmission expansion process (e.g., Section 3.7 of the OATT and the\n1534-Transmission Interconnection Procedures) described in Section 2 of this manual, the NYISO\u2019s\n1535-\u201cInterconnection process\u201d refers to three processes that evaluate proposed interconnections of Large\n",
